# No workarounds or bandaids

When fixing bugs, CI failures, or missing fixtures: **match production**, do not paper over gaps.

## Do

- Align test schemas/fixtures with the real production schema and migrations
- Fix the root cause (missing table, bad contract, incomplete setup)
- Raise clear errors when required state is absent

## Do not

- Swallow errors for missing tables/columns “so tests pass”
- Add silent try/catch no-ops around expected production paths
- Special-case “minimal” or “legacy” DBs unless product explicitly supports that path

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — bandaid so incomplete fixtures keep working
try {
  markPaidOrdersDeliveredForListing(core, opts);
} catch (err) {
  if (/no such table/.test(String(err))) return;
  throw err;
}

// ✅ GOOD — production code assumes the table exists; tests create it
markPaidOrdersDeliveredForListing(core, opts);
```
